      • setStrategy

        @CanIgnoreReturnValue
public DeliveryBuilder setStrategy(DeliveryStrategy strategy)
        Sets strategy of assigning a shard index for a message that is delivered to a particular target.

        If none set, UniformAcrossAllShards.singleShard() is be used.

      • setDeduplicationWindow

        @CanIgnoreReturnValue
public DeliveryBuilder setDeduplicationWindow(com.google.protobuf.Duration deduplicationWindow)
        Sets for how long the previously delivered messages should be kept in the Inbox to ensure the incoming messages aren't duplicates.

        If none set, zero duration is used.

      • setInboxStorage

        @CanIgnoreReturnValue
public DeliveryBuilder setInboxStorage(InboxStorage inboxStorage)
        Sets the custom InboxStorage.

        If none set, the storage is initialized by the StorageFactory specific for this ServerEnvironment.

        If no StorageFactory is present in the ServerEnvironment, a new InMemoryStorageFactory is used.

      • setCatchUpStorage

        @CanIgnoreReturnValue
public DeliveryBuilder setCatchUpStorage(CatchUpStorage catchUpStorage)
        Sets the custom CatchUpStorage.

        If none set, the storage is initialized by the StorageFactory specific for this ServerEnvironment.

        If no StorageFactory is present in the ServerEnvironment, a new InMemoryStorageFactory is used.

      • setMonitor

        @CanIgnoreReturnValue
public DeliveryBuilder setMonitor(DeliveryMonitor monitor)
        Sets the custom DeliveryMonitor.

        If none set, DeliveryMonitor.alwaysContinue() is used.

      • setPageSize

        @CanIgnoreReturnValue
public DeliveryBuilder setPageSize(int pageSize)
        Sets the maximum amount of messages to deliver within a DeliveryStage.

        If none set, DeliveryBuilder.DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE is used.

      • setCatchUpPageSize

        @CanIgnoreReturnValue
public DeliveryBuilder setCatchUpPageSize(int catchUpPageSize)
        Sets the maximum number of events to read from an event store per single read operation during the catch-up.

        If none set, DeliveryBuilder.DEFAULT_CATCH_UP_PAGE_SIZE is used.
